[To quote my colleague Charlie Calisher, a respected arborvirus researcher of many years, "Irrespective of the official statement, unless the error was caused by an alien, it certainly was due to human error. Whether the error was due to a misunderstanding, or was of a technical sort, or for any other reason, this error was a human one." And they occur, sometimes more frequently than we would prefer, whatever our standards. As the press is in a feeding frenzy on this topic, unless something of real significance emerges this thread will be in aestivation. (It is summer time, right?). - Mod.MHJ]
